  <para>After opening up gnumeric, you're presented with a view of a
    worksheet. This is where the majority of the work on the
    spreadsheet is done, and provides access to all the various sub
    dialogs of Gnumeric.</para>
  
  <para>The worksheet view is split into several main areas. The menu
    bar, the button bar, the entry area, the main cell area, and the
    info area. See <xref linkend="worksheet-all-1.jpg"> </para>
  
  <figure id="worksheet-all-1.jpg">
    <title>A example of the entire worksheet.</title>
    <screenshot>
      <graphic fileref="figures/worksheet-all-1.jpg"></graphic>
    </screenshot>
  </figure>
  
 <para>The rest of this chapter will explain all the elements of the worksheet.  </para>

  <sect1 id="menu-bar">
    <title>The Menu bar</title>    
    <para>The default location of the menu bar is the top of the application window.
      It provides a quick and organized access to some of the more common
      operations available.</para>
    
    <sect2>
      
      <!-- IF someone knows a more approriate way to document menu
      options, let me know. This seems a bit excessive, and the output
      from db2html is kind of lame -->
      
      <title><guimenu><accel>F</accel>ile</guimenu></title>
      <para>The <guimenu><accel>F</accel>ile</guimenu> menu contains:</para>
      <variablelist>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>N</accel>ew</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Create a new worksheet. This opens a new
	  worksheet in a window.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>O</accel>pen</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Open an existing worksheet. A new window is
	  created with the file selected in it.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>I</accel>mport</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>S</accel>ave</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Save the current worksheet. If the file has been named and saved before, this
	      will silently save the file to the current filename. If it has not been saved before, this 
	      will prompt for a filename and path.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>S<accel>a</accel>ve as..</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Save a file with a new name. Save a newly created file or save
	      a file with a different name. </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>Print S<accel>e</accel>tup..</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Displays the print setup dialog, from which various 
	  options relating to printing 
          can be configured. This is detailed in <xref linkend="print-setup">.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>P</accel>rint..</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Print the current worksheet. This is detailed in <xref linkend="print">.
	  </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>Print Pre<accel>v</accel>iew..</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Displays a print preview of the current worksheet. This is
          detailed in <xref linkend="print-preview">.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>	
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>Su<accel>m</accel>mary</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Open the summary dialog. Displays a summary of the information about the 
          current workbook.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>C</accel>lose</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Close the current worksheet.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>Q</accel>uit</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Close the open worksheets and quit Gnumeric</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
      </variablelist>  
      
      
    </sect2> 
    
    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu><accel>E</accel>dit</guimenu></title>
      <para>The <guimenu><accel>E</accel>dit</guimenu> menu contains:</para>
      <variablelist>
	
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>U</accel>ndo</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Undoes the last action undertaken.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>R</accel>edo</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Reverses the previous undo operation, restoring 
          the worksheet to its orginal state.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>C</accel>ut</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Remove the content in the currently selected cells and save it.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>C<accel>o</accel>py</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Make a copy of the current selection to be pasted later.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>P</accel>aste</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Paste whatever is in the cut buffer at the cursor.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>P<accel>a</accel>ste Special</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Paste from the cut buffer, but with more options as to what to paste.
	      Useful for pasting just format, or just values, etc.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>S</accel>elect All</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Select every cell in the worksheet.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guisubmenu>Clear -&gt;</guisubmenu></term>
	  <listitem>
	      <variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term><guimenuitem><accel>A</accel>ll</guimenuitem></term>
		  <listitem><para>Clear every cell.</para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term><guimenuitem><accel>F</accel>ormats</guimenuitem></term>
		  <listitem><para>Clear the format from selected cells.</para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term><guimenuitem>Co<accel>m</accel>ments</guimenuitem></term>
		  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term><guimenuitem>C<accel>ontents</accel></guimenuitem></term>
		  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
	      </variablelist>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>S<accel>h</accel>eet</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>S</accel>elect</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>F</accel>ill</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>Search..</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>Search and Replace..</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem><accel>G</accel>oto Cell</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Let the user specify a cell to "jump" to.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><guimenuitem>Recaclculate</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </sect2>
    
    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu><accel>V</accel>iew</guimenu></title>
      <para>The <guimenu><accel>V</accel>iew</guimenu> menu contains:</para>
      <variablelist>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>Z</accel>oom</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Displays the zoom dialog, which allows the zoom level 
            for the workbook to be changed.
	  </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </sect2>
    
    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu><accel>I</accel>nsert</guimenu></title>
      <para>The <guimenu><accel>I</accel>nsert</guimenu> menu contains:</para>
      <variablelist>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>S</accel>heet</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Insert a Sheet in the current workbook.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>C</accel>ells</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Insert a new cell.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>R</accel>ows</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Insert a Row of cells.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem>C<accel>o</accel>lumns</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>Insert a Column of cells.</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem>C<accel>e</accel>lls</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>G</accel>raph</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>O</accel>bject</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>N</accel>ame</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guimenuitem><accel>A</accel>dd / Modify comment</guimenuitem></term>
	  <listitem><para>WriteMe</para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry><term><guisubmenu>S<accel>p</accel>cial</guisubmenu></term>
	  <listitem>
	      <variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term><guimenuitem>Current <accel>d</accel>ate</guimenuitem></term>
		  <listitem><para>Inserts the current date into the currently 
		  selected cell.</para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term><guimenuitem>Current <accel>t</accel>ime</guimenuitem></term>
		  <listitem><para>Inserts the current time into the currently 
		  selected cell.</para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
	      </variablelist>
	      </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </sect2>
    
    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu>F<accel>o</accel>rmat</guimenu></title>
      <para>
        This menu contains:
         <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
           <para>
            <guimenuitem>Cells</guimenuitem>
            &mdash;Open the cell format dialog. Used to change formatting, color, etc. 
           </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guisubmenu>Column-&gt;</guisubmenu>
            &mdash; This submenu contains:
	    <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Auto Fit Selection</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Automatically chooses the optimal size for the column which shows all the text entered.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Width</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Allows the user to adjust the size of the column.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Hide</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Hides the selected columns so that they are not visible.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Unhide</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Makes any columns selected that have being hidden visible again.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Standard Width</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Resizes the columns back to the default width of 6.63.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
           </itemizedlist>
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
           <guisubmenu>Row-&gt;</guisubmenu>
	   &mdash; This sub menu contains:
	    <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Auto Fit Selection</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Automatically chooses the optimal size for the row which shows all the text entered.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Height</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Allows the user to adjust the size of the row.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Hide</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Hides the selected rows so that they are not visible.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Unhide</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Makes any rows selected that have being hidden visible again.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Standard Height</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;Resizes the rows back to the default height of 11.61.
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
           </itemizedlist>
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Sheet-&gt;</guimenuitem>
            &mdash; This sub menu contains:
	    <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Change Name</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Display Formulas</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Hide Zeros</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Hide Gridlines</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Hide Column Header</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                <guimenuitem>Hide Row Header</guimenuitem>
                &mdash;
	        </para>
	      </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Workbook</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;Allows you to configure whether tabs and row and column headers will be shown.
         </para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
       </para>
    </sect2>
    
    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu><accel>T</accel>ools</guimenu></title>
       <para>
        This menu contains:
         <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
           <para>
            <guimenuitem>Plug-ins</guimenuitem>
            &mdash;Displays a list of the plugins currently installed.
           </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Auto Correct</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;Allows the user to configure various auto-correcting functions 
          used when entering data.
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>AutoSave</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;Allows the user to automatically save after a specified number of minutes
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Goal Seek</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;FIXME
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Solver</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;Brings up the Solver Dialog, which can be used to solve linear equations.
          This is detailed in <xref linkend="solver">
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Data Analysis</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;Allows various forms of data analysis to be used on a set of data.
          This is detailed in <xref linkend="analysis-tools">
         </para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
      </para>
    </sect2>
	
    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu><accel>D</accel>ata</guimenu></title>
       <para>
        This menu contains:
         <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
           <para>
            <guimenuitem>Sort</guimenuitem>
            &mdash;Sorts a selection of cells into ascending or descending order, 
            based on the first column selected.
           </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Filter</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;FIXME
         </para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
      </para>
    </sect2>

    <sect2>
      <title><guimenu><accel>H</accel>elp</guimenu></title>
       <para>
        This menu contains:
         <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
           <para>
            <guimenuitem>Gnumeric Manual</guimenuitem>
            &mdash;Display this manual.
           </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>Gnumeric Function Reference</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;View the Gnumeric function reference, a list and description 
          of the functions available in Gnumeric. 
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          <guimenuitem>About</guimenuitem>
          &mdash;hows basic information about Gnumeric, such as the authors' names 
          and the application version number. 
         </para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
      </para>
    </sect2>
  </sect1>
  <!-- end of menubar description -->
  
